reviewText: Terrific duo of fun films that stress romance.  Kate & Leopold is a gem with memorable scenes and a message about true love and finding happiness in life.  Meg Ryan is her usual focused businesswoman.  But Hugh Jackman steals the show.  He's a real hunk.Serendipity is fun, but not as deep or entertaining as Kate & Leopold.  But at the price and linked to K&L;, it's worth having.  Premise in this film is somewhat goofy, but John Cusak makes it work.
Title: Kate & Leopold / Serendipity

reviewText: Have always loved this movie.  Ii had to replace my old copy as borrowed and not returned I would recommend it to anyone
Title: Kate & Leopold / Serendipity

reviewText: I was originally seeking just Serendipity, which is a wonderful movie about the how much your life is impacted by you and by natural occurances (fate).  I am a John Cusack fan and this movie does not diminish his acting ability at all, but rather serves as another opportunity for him to show his scope.  This movie is full of humor and touching moments and an all around good film.  Kate & Leopold is a nice tale in itself about how the past and present can be connected.  I haven't seen it as much, but it's worth a viewing.
Title: Kate & Leopold / Serendipity

reviewText: I bought this DVD because I was looking to purchase Serendipity. I love that movie and it was cheaper to buy it with another movie attached to it. The Kate & Leopold movie was just gravy and it was a cute movie that my wife actually enjoyed. Serendipity is a cute love story.

reviewText: I call it Mind Candy and for a good reason.  You don't have to overthink it, you don't have to worry about plot twists.  You see it for what it is: an escape from reality.  The men are easy to look at, funny and smart.  The women are people you'd like to know - not someone who would completely overshadow you.  These are feel-good movies.  There's nothing wrong with that.
Title: Kate & Leopold / Serendipity

reviewText: I enjoy both of these movies, though Serendipity tends to go on and on before they get there.  For the price compared to the two single prices, this is a bargain and pretty good movies.

reviewText: Two great chick flicks--for less than $5.  In  K & L, Leopold comes forward into the future.  Of course all the women swoon because he is a gentleman in the truest sense of the word!  Serendipity is about a couple that meet and have amazing chemistry.  To test fate, she writes her phone # in a book and sells it to a used book store--if it is meant to be, he will find that book & her.

reviewText: My granddaughter and I watched this on television long ago and recently she mentioned she wanted to see it again.  I found this great double feature on Amazon and purchased it for her.  She watches DVDs in the car when we drive since we live over an hour from her house.  So a round trip is a movie.  She loves this.
